cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.CY, cs.CE, cs.CR 

This paper discusses the standardized processes for efficiently building large financial planning models using spreadsheet programming language. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper also discusses the design practices and quality control, which falls under the category of cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also mentions the mechanistic procedures to construct spreadsheets, which can be categorized under cs.CY (Computational Geometry). Additionally, the paper discusses the professionalization of spreadsheet programming, which can be categorized under cs.CE (Computers and Society). Finally, the paper mentions the enhanced productivity, accuracy, and maintainability for large financial planning models, which can be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
